use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Dez 29, 2022</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104vyw1665702682111.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/vyw1665702682111.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/vyw1665702682111.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"vyw1665702682111\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"vyw1665702682111__uasymsg_401121\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Send an asynchronous message to a local Uniface application.</p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"vyw1665702682111__topic_d118685e1_d118686e1_d118687e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vyw1665702682111__p_d118688e1_d118689e1_d118690e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">long uasymsg (long</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">pid</var>, <code class=\"ph codeph\">char*</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">destkey</var>, <code class=\"ph codeph\">char*</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">message</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">);</code>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"vyw1665702682111__topic_d84677e1_d84678e1_d84679e1_d84680e1_d84681e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d780685e80\">Parameters</h2>\n<dl class=\"dl parml\" id=\"vyw1665702682111__parml_kd5_c1s_zvb\">\n<dt class=\"dt pt dlterm\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">pid</var></dt>\n<dd class=\"dd pd\">Process Id of the Uniface process to which the message must be sent.</dd>\n<dt class=\"dt pt dlterm\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">destkey</var></dt>\n<dd class=\"dd pd\">Obsolete. Always use the value zero.</dd>\n<dt class=\"dt pt dlterm\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">message</var></dt>\n<dd class=\"dd pd\">Message to send. The message must not be longer than 249 bytes.</dd>\n</dl>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"vyw1665702682111__topic_d84682e1_d84683e1_d84684e1_d84685e1_d84686e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d780685e120\">Return Values</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"vyw1665702682111__table_d14798e1_d14799e1_d14800e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Values returned by uasymsg</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"vyw1665702682111__table_d14798e1_d14799e1_d14800e1__entry__1\">Value</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"vyw1665702682111__table_d14798e1_d14799e1_d14800e1__entry__2\">Meaning</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vyw1665702682111__table_d14798e1_d14799e1_d14800e1__entry__1\">1</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vyw1665702682111__table_d14798e1_d14799e1_d14800e1__entry__2\">The message was successfully sent.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vyw1665702682111__table_d14798e1_d14799e1_d14800e1__entry__1\">-1</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vyw1665702682111__table_d14798e1_d14799e1_d14800e1__entry__2\">The call failed. The message was not\n                        sent.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"vyw1665702682111__topic_d84687e1_d84688e1_d84689e1_d84690e1_d84691e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d780685e172\">Use</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vyw1665702682111__p_d118709e1_d118710e1_d118711e1\">Unix platforms only (except Tru64 Unix), in library <span class=\"ph filepath\">ulib</span>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"vyw1665702682111__topic_d84692e1_d84693e1_d84694e1_d84695e1_d84696e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d780685e185\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vyw1665702682111__p_d118715e1_d118716e1_d118717e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">uasymsg</code> sends a string message to the Uniface process identified by\n               <var class=\"keyword varname\">pid</var>. That application must be listening to asynchronous messages,\n            that is, it must have called <code class=\"ph codeph\">uasync</code> or be using the assignment setting\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">$IPC_ASYNC</code>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\">Strictly speaking, <code class=\"ph codeph\">uasymsg</code> does not send the message, it just puts it\n            into an IPC message queue, the key of that queue being equal to the\n               <var class=\"keyword varname\">pid</var> of the receiving process. It does not check whether that\n            process or queue actually exists. If the <var class=\"keyword varname\">pid</var> is wrong, or the process\n            does not listen for asynchronous messages, <code class=\"ph codeph\">uasymsg</code> will create the\n            queue and write the message to it, and that queue will just sit there, never to be read\n            or removed.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vyw1665702682111__p_d118718e1_d118719e1_d118720e1\">To enable sending a message without having to write 3GL code, Uniface provides the program <code class=\"ph codeph\">pidfmess</code>, which has the same functionality as <code class=\"ph codeph\">uasymsg</code>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\">The following example sends a message to a Uniface application with\n            process Id 12345:</p>\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104vyw1665702682111_html_0\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"vyw1665702682111__codeblock_z5r_p1s_zvb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">uasymsg(12345, 0, \"Here's a message for process id 12345\");</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/snx1665702681980.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>uasync</a><p>Initialize the Uniface application to receive asynchronous messages.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lla1665702682181.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>unoasync</a><p>Disable the handling of asynchronous messages by the application.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533248\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533248\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "uasymsg Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Dez 29, 2022 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Send an asynchronous message to a local Uniface application. long uasymsg (long pid , char* destkey , char* message ); Parameters pid Process Id of the Uniface process to which the message must be sent. destkey Obsolete. Always use the value zero. message Message to send. The message must not be longer than 249 bytes. Return Values Table 1. Values returned by uasymsg Value Meaning 1 The message was successfully sent. -1 The call failed. The message was not sent. Use Unix platforms only (except Tru64 Unix), in library ulib Description uasymsg sends a string message to the Uniface process identified by pid . That application must be listening to asynchronous messages, that is, it must have called uasync or be using the assignment setting $IPC_ASYNC . Strictly speaking, uasymsg does not send the message, it just puts it into an IPC message queue, the key of that queue being equal to the pid of the receiving process. It does not check whether that process or queue actually exists. If the pid is wrong, or the process does not listen for asynchronous messages, uasymsg will create the queue and write the message to it, and that queue will just sit there, never to be read or removed. To enable sending a message without having to write 3GL code, Uniface provides the program pidfmess , which has the same functionality as uasymsg . The following example sends a message to a Uniface application with process Id 12345: Explain this code uasymsg(12345, 0, \"Here's a message for process id 12345\"); Copy Related Links uasync Initialize the Uniface application to receive asynchronous messages. unoasync Disable the handling of asynchronous messages by the application. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}